description:
Wildlife - Episode 2: Just Penguins | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'Wildlife - Episode 3' here: https://youtu.be/eiqeZwk7NhI

This documentary marvels at the wondrous parade naturally staged by these quirky, yet distinguished two-toned marine creatures. March, hop, and swim along with the 18 members of this much-loved family of torpedo-shaped, flightless birds that can be found in many waters of the Southern Hemisphere, as well as the equatorial Galapagos Islands. Devoted partners, doting parents, and clever hunters, Penguins are a sight to behold when they gather in colonies that can number in the hundreds of thousands.

Experience the wonder of captivating documentaries in this engaging series, exploring the lives and behaviors of some of the planet's most incredible animals. From Monkeys and Penguins to Sharks, Marsupials, Wild Cats, Reptiles, Wild Dogs, Insects, Hooved Mammals, and Octopuses, each episode delves into the world of a specific group, providing a thorough exploration of their fascinating existence. Enjoy a visual feast with high-quality archive footage, showcasing rare behaviors, intimate close-ups, and fast-paced action sequences. Uncover the extraordinary physical attributes, sensory perceptions, communication skills, and ingenious adaptations of a diverse array of creatures, both great and small.

Free Documentary is dedicated to bringing high-class documentaries to you on YouTube for free with the latest camera equipment used by well-known filmmakers working for famous production studios. You will see fascinating shots from the deep seas and up in the air, capturing great stories and pictures of everything our beautiful and interesting planet offers. 

Enjoy stories about nature, wildlife, culture, people, history, and more to come.
